  "elapsed_s": 4.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] And I was-- went to school to the nuns in Rochester, New York.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They gave us really a wonderful training, and many of the students in the school were Catholic, Protestant, Jewish, whatever, you know?",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But it was-- the nuns had charge of the training.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Now, there are hardly any nuns left.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So it has become almost publicly owned-- the school, Nazareth College in Rochester.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But it has a very high reputation.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, at that time, before World War II, there weren't so very many Negroes in the upper part of America.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And like anything strange, people didn't know well any Negroes.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We had a couple of Negroes in our school, in the public schools of Rochester-- there was good training together in the-- in the school system.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But I would say Eisenhower, World War I-- World War II, and the immediate post-war have made many changes in any feeling of color, racial antagonisms, and so forth-- have changed things very much from those days.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "To tell you the truth, I wouldn't know which ones were Jewish and which weren't.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was not much of a point with any of us, you know?",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But there were quite a few interesting Jewish people in Rochester, New York, where we were centered-- Rochester, New York.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And it was because of some of these people-- I personally didn't happen to know them-- that I went to Europe, and my life changed quite a bit.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They had relatives in Germany who wanted to prepare themselves, should Hitler be going to stay, to get out of it and come to their relatives in America.",
      "word_count": 28
    }
  ],
